HEADWORD: Red-tailed
<hw>Red"-tailed`</hw> <pr>(-t?ld`)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having a red
tail.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Red-tailed hawk</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a large
North American hawk (<spn>Buteo borealis</spn>). When adult its tail is
chestnut red. Called also <altname>hen hawck</altname>, and
<altname>red-tailed buzzard</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Red-tape</ent>⟦br⟧
